# Supabase Rules (this repo)

## Where Supabase is configured
- Browser client: `src/utils/supabase/client.ts` (`createBrowserClient`)
- Server client: `src/utils/supabase/server.ts`
- Constants: `src/utils/supabase/constants.ts` (**do not add hardcoded secrets here — see security-secrets rule**)
- Data provider wiring: `src/providers/data-provider/index.ts` (uses `@refinedev/supabase`)
- Auth provider wiring:
  - client: `src/providers/auth-provider/auth-provider.client.ts`
  - server: `src/providers/auth-provider/auth-provider.server.ts`

## Client vs server boundaries
- **Client Components** (`"use client"`) must use the browser client (`supabaseBrowserClient`).
- **Server Components / Route handlers / middleware** must use the server client utilities.
- Never import a server-only module into a client component.

## Data access rules
- App CRUD should go through Refine hooks + `dataProvider` (preferred).
- Direct Supabase calls are allowed only inside the provider layer (`src/providers/**`) and Supabase utils (`src/utils/supabase/**`).
- **The data provider (`src/providers/data-provider/index.ts`) is marked `"use client"` and uses `supabaseBrowserClient` — all Refine CRUD operations run client-side only.** Do not expect Refine hooks to work in Server Components. If you need server-side data fetching, use `createSupabaseServerClient()` from `src/utils/supabase/server.ts` directly inside a Server Component or Route Handler.

## Query shape
- If you need joins/selects, prefer passing `meta.select` through Refine hooks (example: `meta: { select: "*, categories(id,title)" }`).
- Do not pair `meta.select` joins with `useMany` for the same relation — pick one. See `pages.mdc` for details.

## Middleware (`src/middleware.ts`)
- `src/middleware.ts` is the **first line of auth defence** — it refreshes the Supabase session cookie on every request using `src/utils/supabase/middleware.ts`.
- Do not remove or bypass the `updateSession` call in middleware.
- Do not add application logic (redirects, data fetching) directly to middleware beyond session refresh — use Refine `authProvider.check` for route-level guards.
- The middleware `matcher` config controls which routes it runs on; update it carefully if adding new public routes.

## Auth rules
- Auth-related redirects and checks should use Refine `authProvider` contract (`login/logout/check/getIdentity/getPermissions`).
- Don't duplicate auth logic in page components.
